body:
This PR fixes https://github.com/filecoin-project/rust-fil-proofs/issues/1605. As it is stated in its title it bumps toolchain to 1.59.0 as `async-global-executor v2.1.0` which is one of dependencies now requires mentioned version of rust compiler.

One can be noticed that `cargo clippy` becomes more aggressive and for the new version of `rustc` it treats many of previous warnings as errors, so I had to fix all that issues in order to achieve green CI mark. More specifically, I had to 
- drop some "never-read" fields;
- to remove couple command line arguments (from CLI tools) tied to "never-read" values; 
- add some other "requested" refactoring.
